text.paragraph:
Continued depression of the myocardium with beta-blocking agents over a period of time can, in some cases, lead to cardiac failure. At the first sign or symptom of impending cardiac failure, patients should be treated appropriately according to 
currently recommended guidelines, and the response observed closely. If cardiac failure continues despite adequate treatment, atenolol tablet, USP, should be withdrawn. (See DOSAGE AND ADMINISTRATION
).
